  "text": "It would be interesting to see if the studied problems can be formulated and solved, for example, for countably infinite or continuous support sets. (ii) Applications: Arikan showed an application of the guessing problem in a sequential decoding problem [CITATION_1] . Humblet showed that cumulants of code-lengths in Campbell's problem has applications in minimizing the probability of buffer overflow in source coding problems [CITATION_2] . We would like to see if other potential applications emerge from this unified study.",
